We spent about an hour today chasing a phantom Pigeon 2 drift issue.

When robot is on the cart, and we turn the cart, we see a huge drift that happen pretty frequently. Some 90 degree turns of the cart and back seem to lose as much as 20 degrees at times (meaning - say, IMU is at 0; turn 45, turn 90, turn back to 60, back to 30, back to 0 - IMU shows as much as 20).

We even changed a Pigeon2 to another one - same thing.

However, we put robot on the floor - no IMU drift (???). Drives fine. We rotated back and forth, FAST, slow - no drift. Did lateral movements - everything holds.

Any ideas why our cart seems to be cursed?

The EnableCompass is disabled by default -

api.ctr-electronics.com

Pigeon2FeaturesConfigs (CTRE Phoenix 6 Java 25.3.0)

declaration: package: com.ctre.phoenix6.configs, class: Pigeon2FeaturesConfigs

and we definitely do not enable it. I mean - I will check on the actual Pigeon tonight, but I do not believe we enable it to begin with.
